{
  "concentration": "Health and Human Biology",
  "slug": "hhbi",
  "url": "https://bulletin.brown.edu/the-college/concentrations/hhbi/",
  "description": "Health and Human Biology is an interdisciplinary concentration that provides a rigorous foundation in the biological sciences with substantive course work in humanities and social sciences within a subfield of Human Health and Disease. The program includes: background courses, biology core courses, a set of theme courses, and a Senior Capstone activity. Background courses provide the essential foundations in chemistry, mathematics, methods, and basic biology. These support the Biology core, which is comprised of a flexible menu of intermediate and advanced courses. A required portion of the Biology core is Genetics, a cornerstone of human biology and its interface with other fields. The Biology core underscores the related coursework within the Health and Disease Theme.\u00a0 The Theme courses are social science and humanities courses that form a cohesive, thoughtful grouping.\u00a0 Theme groupings must be approved by the advisor. A required senior capstone course or activity builds on the program's focus. CAPSTONE:Seehttps://www.brown.edu/academics/biology/undergraduate-education/undergraduate/health-and-human-biologyfor more information on the Capstone Activity.",
